FT  13 AUG 94 / Brittany Ferries joins livestock ban
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Another leading ferry operator is to cease carrying live animals for
slaughter because of fears over the suffering caused.
Brittany Ferries said it would stop exports of farm animals, except those
for fattening or breeding, on its six routes to France and Spain from August
22.
