<HEADLINE>
FT  12 AUG 94 / International Company News: Czech bank rallies after heavy
loss
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VINCENT BOLAND
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PRAGUE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Agrobanka, the Czech Republic's fifth biggest bank, posted a loss of Kcs3bn
(Dollars 107m) last year after making a big increase in loan-loss
provisions, to Kcs4bn. However, the bank said it had recovered in the first
half of the current year with a profit of Kcs99m.
The 1993 loss announced yesterday wiped out the bank's capital, leaving it
with a negative equity of Kcs400m and with a negative capital adequacy ratio
of -0.8 per cent.
The Czech National Bank, the central banking authority, has set a minimum
adequacy ration of 8 per cent.
