<HEADLINE>
FT  12 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Losses widen at Unit Group
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Losses at Unit Group, the USM-quoted pallet maker, widened from Pounds
388,000 to Pounds 1.66m in the year to end-March.
The deficit was split between trading losses of Pounds 1.07m, and closure
and reorganisation costs of Pounds 580,000. During the year the company
consolidated operations on a single site at Golborne, Warrington.
Turnover fell from Pounds 18.9m to Pounds 16.8m.
At the end of May, Unit raised Pounds 1.26m before expenses through a
subscription and rights issue which, together with the sale of a former
engineering site, helped cut gearing from 135 per cent to 34 per cent. Mr
John Adams, chairman, said: 'The group is now operating comfortably within
its existing banking facilities.
'The immediate priorities are to achieve a further reduction in operating
costs, improve production efficiency and recover increased timber costs by
price increases.'
Losses per share were 29.8p (6.3p) and again no dividend is proposed.
</TEXT>
