<HEADLINE>
FT  12 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Terms agreed for Leeds shopping mall
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Land Securities is to build a shopping centre with an estimated development
cost of Pounds 100m at Churwell, Leeds.
Land has reached agreement with White Rose (Leeds), a joint venture company
between a subsidiary of Yorkshire Water and Evans of Leeds, the property
company.
Land will take a 999 year lease of the land in return for a share in the net
rental income of the centre once it is opened.
