FT  12 AUG 94 / Main points of Offer's review
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Distribution prices to fall by 11 per cent to 17 per cent next year, and 2
percentage points below inflation for the four following years
Average household bill to fall Pounds12 - Pounds16 in first year with a
saving of Pounds70 - Pounds90 over the five years. Total saving for all
consumers of Pounds2.5bn
Controls allow for 'substantially higher investment' but 10 per cent less
than electricity companies were planning
Companies have until September 30 to accept new controls or appeal to MMC
Prices to be based on previous year's inflation rate rather than forecast of
coming year's
Cost of capital assumed to be 7 per cent before tax
New measures to encourage energy efficiency and cut power losses
Standards of service on supply restoration and meter reading to be raised
Controls assume cuts in wage bills, though chairmen's salaries are 'a matter
for the companies not the regulator'
