FT  12 AUG 94 / Cumbria urges N-waste inquiry
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL CHEESERIGHT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Cumbria county councillors decided yesterday to ask Mr John Gummer, the
environment secretary, to call in the planning application by Nirex, the
nuclear industry's waste disposal company, for a Pounds 120m rock laboratory
beneath Sellafield.
The council believes consideration of the plans, which would study the
geology of the site for Nirex's proposed Pounds 2b underground nuclear waste
repository, should be part of a wide-ranging public inquiry into the whole
issue of nuclear waste disposal.
