FT  12 AUG 94 / Barclaycard to build Pounds 45m HQ on business park site
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL CHEESERIGHT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Barclaycard, the credit-card issuer owned by Barclays Bank, is to spend
about Pounds 45m on building a new headquarters at the Northampton Business
Park, Paul Cheeseright writes.
The headquarters will bring together, on the outskirts of Northampton, staff
split between three leased buildings in the town centre. Barclaycard's 2,600
employees make it Northampton's largest employer. Barclays said contracts
had been exchanged for the purchase of 18 acres at the business park, where
the asking price for land is Pounds 350,000 an acre.
Northampton Business Park is in the hands of the receiver, Mr Robin Addy of
Coopers &amp; Lybrand. Mr Addy was appointed by a consortium of banks, not
including Barclays, when UK Land, the property company developing the park,
collapsed in 1991.
